Title: Series: The Large Passion
Description: The flight to Egypt; Mary with the infant Jesus on a mule, accompanied by Joseph who is walking; plate within border cut and damaged on both sides; with ornamental border; illustration to 'Historia Christi Patiensis ac Morientis' (Johannes Mommart: Brussels, 1651). 1511 Woodcut
Producer name: Print made by: Jacob Cornelisz. van Oostsanen
Curator's comments: This is fourth edition; for comment see 1911,0708.33.
